The paper discusses methods for aggregating crowd labels to estimate true labels, which is a common problem in human computation via crowdsourcing. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses statistical models and algorithms for making inference on these models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses adaptive methods for iteratively collecting labels, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
